==English==

===Etymology===
From the proverb "When he should get aught, each finger is a thumb." from John Heywood's Collection
of 1546.

===Adjective===
'''[[all]] [[thumbs]]'''
#{{idiom}} [[clumsy|Clumsy]]; [[awkward]]; not [[dextrous]].
#: ''I am '''all thumbs''' when it comes to shuffling cards.''

===Related terms===
*[[thumb]]
*[[mostly thumbs]]

